import java.util.*;
class Codechef{
	public static void main (String[] args) throws java.lang.Exception{
		Scanner sc = new Scanner(System.in);
        int t = sc.nextInt();
        while(t-->0){
            int n = sc.nextInt();
            System.out.print(1+" ");
            System.out.print(1+" ");
            System.out.println((n-2)+" ");
        }
	}
}

LOGIC---
We are asked to keep two numbers same and at least one number odd.
Also, constraint is n>=4
So, if one number is 1 -> odd
let's have other number -> 1 again

Left number -> n-2

So, we got two equal number na dat least one odd => makign the above numbers always true
